22	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
23	// Week 6.5e acceptance test — @ax/mcp-client end-to-end.
24	//
25	// Exercises the full MCP slice against a real stdio subprocess (the
26	// `@ax/test-harness` stub spawned via `node <path>`):
27	//
28	//   host (this test process)
29	//     ├── @ax/mcp-client plugin on init
30	//     │     ├── loadConfigs() from @ax/storage-sqlite
31	//     │     └── StdioClientTransport → node <mcpServerStubPath> (real spawn)
32	//     ├── @ax/sandbox-subprocess spawns
33	//     │     └── @ax/agent-native-runner
34	//     │           └── HTTP POST /llm.call → @ax/llm-proxy-anthropic-format
35	//     │                 └── bus.call('llm:call') → stub LLM plugin (below)
36	//     └── runner sees `mcp.echo.echo` in the tool catalog, emits a tool_use,
37	//         which loops back as POST /tool.execute-host → `tool:execute:mcp.echo.echo`
38	//         → `McpConnection.callTool('echo', ...)` → subprocess stdout → MCP reply
39	//
40	// What we verify:
41	//   1. Round-trip: tool:pre-call + tool:post-call fire on the host with the
42	//      namespaced name (`mcp.echo.echo`), chat ends cleanly (rc === 0), and
43	//      the echoed payload literally round-trips the 'acceptance' substring.
